The paper discusses a protocol for performing larger computations on a resource-constrained environment like a blockchain in a trusted way. This involves incentivizing participants to verify computations and countering sybil attacks. These topics are relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including cryptography (cs.CR), distributed computing (cs.DC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), programming languages (cs.PL), and machine learning (cs.LG). However, since the paper focuses on the incentive mechanism for the protocol, cs.CR and cs.DC are the most likely sub-categories.
